1
00:01:02,478 --> 00:01:06,898
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:09,270
my day starts.

3
00:01:33,406 --> 00:01:36,996
My diner is open from midnight
to seven in the morning.

4
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:42,055
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:43,938 --> 00:01:45,588
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

6
00:01:45,588 --> 00:01:47,048
That's all I have on my menu.

7
00:01:47,817 --> 00:01:50,277
But I make whatever customers request

8
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:52,775
as long as I have ingredients for it.

9
00:01:53,112 --> 00:01:54,692
That's my policy.

10
00:01:59,702 --> 00:02:03,202
Do I even have customers?
More than you would expect.

11
00:02:06,158 --> 00:02:08,938
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

12
00:02:08,939 --> 00:02:14,337
TAN-MEN

13
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:38,617
I use instant dried noodles for ramen.

14
00:02:39,368 --> 00:02:41,538
But for tan-men, I use fresh noodles.

15
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:44,544
They are better suited
for tan-men.

16
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:54,216
I feel guilty eating ramen at night.

17
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,880
Tan-men is good since
it comes with veggies.

18
00:02:57,322 --> 00:02:58,452
Here you go again.

19
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:02,760
If you're going to make excuses,
just don't eat it at all.

20
00:03:03,307 --> 00:03:06,687
It's like life. We can't make
rational choices all the time.

21
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:11,392
Be careful.
It's that extra bite that makes you fat.

22
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,790
Mr. Shimada is a radio announcer.

23
00:03:17,238 --> 00:03:22,458
I guess his doctor had told him
to watch his weight.

24
00:03:26,249 --> 00:03:27,119
Welcome.

25
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,390
Hi.

26
00:03:35,257 --> 00:03:36,797
Tan-men, no noodles.

27
00:03:37,601 --> 00:03:38,561
Got it.

28
00:03:45,224 --> 00:03:47,514
Here you go. Without noodles.

29
00:03:48,391 --> 00:03:49,511
Thank you.

30
00:04:05,699 --> 00:04:06,734
Excuse me.

31
00:04:07,751 --> 00:04:09,741
I've never heard of such a dish.

32
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:15,050
I don't want to have carbohydrates
late at night.

33
00:04:16,025 --> 00:04:16,945
Besides,

34
00:04:17,693 --> 00:04:19,023
noodles get soggy

35
00:04:19,756 --> 00:04:21,846
while I eat the vegetables.

36
00:04:22,148 --> 00:04:25,068
Well, that makes sense, but...

37
00:04:25,749 --> 00:04:28,260
Master, cancel my order of rice with tea.

38
00:04:28,260 --> 00:04:30,915
I will have tan-men without noodles,
just like her.

39
00:04:30,915 --> 00:04:31,745
Sure.

40
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,270
Are you done for the night?

41
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:41,442
Not yet. I will work until morning.

42
00:04:42,531 --> 00:04:44,398
I'm so impressed by you.

43
00:04:44,398 --> 00:04:46,322
I have no sense of direction.

44
00:04:47,119 --> 00:04:49,379
Do you use a navigation system?

45
00:04:50,768 --> 00:04:53,478
I know every street in Tokyo.

46
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,960
Without noodles, huh?

47
00:04:58,923 --> 00:05:02,906
Mr. Shimada was so impressed that...

48
00:05:02,906 --> 00:05:03,551
MIDNIGHT SHIMA-CHAN

49
00:05:03,551 --> 00:05:07,929
Hi Ms. Witch of Tabata,
I've also tried every method.

50
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:10,913
There's one called the Apple Diet.

51
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:13,222
Don't try it. It didn't fill me up at all.

52
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:18,356
So I switched to eating apple pies,
but then I got even fatter.

53
00:05:18,748 --> 00:05:20,578
It all went straight to my gut.

54
00:05:22,154 --> 00:05:26,704
Anyway, "without" at a noodle shop
means tempura soba without noodles.

55
00:05:26,877 --> 00:05:28,957
If someone orders that with a drink,

56
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:31,745
I know he's a real connoisseur.

57
00:05:32,542 --> 00:05:34,172
Recently I met someone

58
00:05:34,695 --> 00:05:38,655
who ordered tan-men without noodles
at my favorite diner.

59
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:44,763
Tan-men without noodles
is basically hearty vegetable soup.

60
00:05:45,189 --> 00:05:49,014
It would be a great meal
for someone who is watching their weight.

61
00:05:49,014 --> 00:05:53,314
Really? What a strange dish to order.

62
00:05:55,771 --> 00:05:56,931
You're right.

63
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:59,406
<i>But I have not tried it yet.</i>

64
00:06:01,735 --> 00:06:04,445
Was it about this diner?

65
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:07,530
That's right.
It was Mr. Shimada's radio show.

66
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,780
He talked about tan-men without noodles.

67
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:12,740
That was about Ms. Harumi, right?

68
00:06:12,928 --> 00:06:15,805
- That's right.
- Who is she?

69
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:19,089
Don't you remember?
The female taxi driver.

70
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:22,000
That good-looking woman
who is past her prime?

71
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,157
Past her prime? How old is she?

72
00:06:24,341 --> 00:06:26,091
My guess is...

73
00:06:26,218 --> 00:06:29,308
- she is in her mid-forties.
- She is young enough for me then.

74
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:31,918
I wouldn't even call her mature.

75
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:36,143
I have a thing for women
with low metabolic rates.

76
00:06:36,376 --> 00:06:38,886
I get a strong libido for such women.

77
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:40,988
You will live long.

78
00:06:41,871 --> 00:06:45,081
Can I try tan-men without noodles?

79
00:06:45,201 --> 00:06:47,701
- Me, too.
- Sure.

80
00:06:49,736 --> 00:06:51,326
Can I? You look mellow.

81
00:06:52,276 --> 00:06:54,001
- Here's one.
- Mellow?

82
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:56,245
- One more.
- Shut up.

83
00:06:59,837 --> 00:07:03,007
Two weeks later...

84
00:07:08,719 --> 00:07:11,439
I knew it. It was about me, huh?

85
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:15,556
I'm sorry for using your story
without your permission.

86
00:07:15,851 --> 00:07:20,021
The way you were eating
made the dish look so tasty.

87
00:07:21,335 --> 00:07:23,215
It reminded me of this one time...

88
00:07:23,958 --> 00:07:26,153
I called into a show to request a song,

89
00:07:26,153 --> 00:07:27,733
and my name was mentioned.

90
00:07:28,278 --> 00:07:29,988
The late-night-radio generation!

91
00:07:30,464 --> 00:07:32,134
Now you know how old I am.

92
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,913
So, why a radio jockey?

93
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:40,508
I looked up to late-night radio jockeys.

94
00:07:41,585 --> 00:07:43,465
When I got sad or stressed out,

95
00:07:43,983 --> 00:07:45,653
and didn't know what to do,

96
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:49,090
they helped me feel like I wasn't alone.

97
00:07:51,092 --> 00:07:52,882
I know what you mean.

98
00:08:00,354 --> 00:08:01,184
Yes.

99
00:08:02,815 --> 00:08:03,645
Sure.

100
00:08:04,191 --> 00:08:06,311
I'm nearby.

101
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,736
I will pick you up in five minutes.

102
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:11,572
See you at the same spot.

103
00:08:12,616 --> 00:08:13,906
See you soon.

104
00:08:17,991 --> 00:08:19,371
Is that a regular customer?

105
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:21,792
Regular customers are great.

106
00:08:22,146 --> 00:08:25,276
It's not always easy finding customers
just by driving around.

107
00:08:26,505 --> 00:08:28,215
Master, check please.

108
00:08:30,926 --> 00:08:32,886
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you.

109
00:08:44,189 --> 00:08:47,489
Why does she looks so familiar to me?

110
00:08:50,738 --> 00:08:51,603
Right?

111
00:08:51,603 --> 00:08:54,915
Don't you think they look alike?
I have no doubt.

112
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:56,457
Crimson Maple.

113
00:08:58,912 --> 00:09:00,702
They do look alike.

114
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:02,243
What is this anyway?

115
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:05,006
She's Crimson Maple.

116
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:08,018
From the legendary TV show,
Super Ninja Squadron Koga.

117
00:09:08,018 --> 00:09:09,006
Do you know it?

118
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:12,216
No. There were too many
ninja squadron shows.

119
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,251
Black Flying Squirrel,

120
00:09:16,251 --> 00:09:20,280
Ultramarine Gale, Light-green Yonezo,
Orange Tasuke,

121
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,982
and Crimson Maple.

122
00:09:24,563 --> 00:09:28,903
Five super ninjas kill evildoers,
leaving no trace!

123
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:34,944
When I was a kid, I sent her a fan letter.

124
00:09:35,078 --> 00:09:37,168
Then she sent me this photo.

125
00:09:39,188 --> 00:09:41,148
I wonder if she remembers me.

126
00:09:46,293 --> 00:09:47,873
Mr. Middle-aged Rider,

127
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,960
there is no age limit for falling in love.

128
00:09:51,298 --> 00:09:53,308
But don't be a stalker.

129
00:09:53,425 --> 00:09:55,675
Please consider
how your love interest feels.

130
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,010
Speaking of love...

131
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:03,899
I recently ran into my first love
at the most random place.

132
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:07,558
Unfortunately,
it was an unrequited love.

133
00:10:07,558 --> 00:10:10,148
She doesn't even know who I am.

134
00:10:11,036 --> 00:10:14,826
Some of you may remember a TV show
called Super Ninja Squadron Koga,

135
00:10:15,239 --> 00:10:18,499
which was popular when I was a kid.

136
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:21,744
One of the show's characters,
Crimson Maple,

137
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:23,582
is my first love.

138
00:10:24,435 --> 00:10:26,452
When I knew
that she was Crimson Maple,

139
00:10:26,453 --> 00:10:28,913
this song started playing in my head.

140
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:33,883
It's the main theme song
from Super Ninja Squadron Koga.

141
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:41,724
That brings back so many memories.

142
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:44,017
Are you starting a fan club for that show?

143
00:10:44,017 --> 00:10:44,935
That's right.

144
00:10:44,935 --> 00:10:48,232
I announced it on my website
to see the listeners' reactions.

145
00:10:48,232 --> 00:10:50,075
The feedback was amazing.

146
00:10:50,076 --> 00:10:53,184
My favorite episode is when the leader
welcomed Maple,

147
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:54,920
a lone ninja, to their squadron.

148
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:57,232
- "If It Is Hidden, It Is The Flower."
- Yes!

149
00:10:57,232 --> 00:10:58,532
Flying Squirrel says...

150
00:10:59,116 --> 00:11:00,456
"We got your back.

151
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:02,411
So don't run. Just fight."

152
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:03,238
PLAYING NEXT WEEK?!

153
00:11:03,238 --> 00:11:05,238
Even as a kid, I was so moved.

154
00:11:05,238 --> 00:11:06,545
I felt the same way.

155
00:11:06,545 --> 00:11:09,209
And Flying Squirrel and...

156
00:11:09,209 --> 00:11:11,003
Men...

157
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:12,333
never grow up.

158
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:14,710
Here you go.

159
00:11:15,507 --> 00:11:17,557
Extra large pork and veggie soup combo.

160
00:11:19,261 --> 00:11:20,261
Bon appétit.

161
00:11:21,474 --> 00:11:22,717
Hey, guys.

162
00:11:23,348 --> 00:11:25,108
It's great to show your support,

163
00:11:25,282 --> 00:11:28,532
but have you thought about
how she would feel?

164
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:30,646
Don't you agree, Master?

165
00:11:31,064 --> 00:11:31,894
Yeah...

166
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:35,775
I'm sure many things have
led her to where she is now.

167
00:11:36,528 --> 00:11:40,748
And that's what I want her to
talk about on my show.

168
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:45,370
She's diligent, and loyal to her job.

169
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:48,331
I felt it when I met her.
It's just a hunch, but...

170
00:11:49,186 --> 00:11:52,961
I think she could even talk about
her downs positively.

171
00:11:52,961 --> 00:11:55,541
That's right.
She must have moved on by now.

172
00:11:55,732 --> 00:11:58,062
She is a good taxi driver now.

173
00:11:58,383 --> 00:12:00,741
I'm sure her past is just
a fond memory now.

174
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,483
It's a fond memory for you,

175
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:07,356
but it's not for me.

176
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:11,733
I didn't like the role to begin with.

177
00:12:13,972 --> 00:12:17,047
No matter who I played,
I was always Maple of Koga.

178
00:12:19,112 --> 00:12:21,612
That's the main reason why I quit acting.

179
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:24,784
I didn't know that.

180
00:12:25,410 --> 00:12:27,870
I've been through a lot to be here now.

181
00:12:28,872 --> 00:12:31,045
Don't expose my life
for your own interest.

182
00:12:31,181 --> 00:12:32,431
That wasn't my...

183
00:12:33,168 --> 00:12:34,168
But...

184
00:12:34,461 --> 00:12:36,041
I understand your point.

185
00:12:37,003 --> 00:12:38,083
I'm really sorry.

186
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,810
Master, another one.

187
00:13:01,446 --> 00:13:04,906
What's the occasion?
You've never had a drink here.

188
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,326
Does Mr. Shimada still visit?

189
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:13,622
Speaking of... he hasn't in a while.

190
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:19,008
I...

191
00:13:19,829 --> 00:13:22,499
can finally tell everyone with pride...

192
00:13:23,218 --> 00:13:24,808
how much I love my current job.

193
00:13:26,346 --> 00:13:28,096
Mr. Shimada said the same thing.

194
00:13:29,198 --> 00:13:32,578
"She's diligent, and loyal to her job."

195
00:13:35,355 --> 00:13:36,185
Is that right?

196
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:43,281
Master, "without noodles" please.

197
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,288
Sure.

198
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:03,920
Back then,
I was the worst actress in the group.

199
00:14:04,347 --> 00:14:05,937
I didn't want to admit it.

200
00:14:07,262 --> 00:14:08,932
So I put myself on a pedestal,

201
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:11,148
and took my stress out on others.

202
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,147
I was really awful.

203
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:20,905
But even then,
the leader always defended me.

204
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:25,443
What's the name of his character?

205
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:27,869
Flying Squirrel.

206
00:14:28,575 --> 00:14:29,745
That's right.

207
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:34,953
Flying Squirrel was a good man, huh?

208
00:14:39,586 --> 00:14:40,716
I loved with him.

209
00:14:43,882 --> 00:14:44,712
But then...

210
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:50,553
Good morning.

211
00:14:54,428 --> 00:14:57,508
One day I went to the studio
earlier than usual.

212
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,073
I...

213
00:15:14,725 --> 00:15:15,645
Sorry.

214
00:15:21,169 --> 00:15:23,241
This one is on me.

215
00:15:23,241 --> 00:15:26,514
No, you really don't need to do that.

216
00:15:26,514 --> 00:15:27,633
Please, let me.

217
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:31,306
He wished he had been born a girl.

218
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,300
He confided in me about it.

219
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,398
Thanks to that,
I couldn't be in love with him,

220
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:41,894
but I got an indispensable friendship.

221
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,506
Here you go.

222
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:52,284
We didn't have much money...

223
00:15:53,605 --> 00:15:56,265
so we always had a drink with this dish.

224
00:16:00,453 --> 00:16:03,935
I was afraid that old fans
might scrutinize his current life

225
00:16:03,936 --> 00:16:05,924
if the show renewed their interest.

226
00:16:08,445 --> 00:16:10,295
Since he protected me back then,

227
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:12,300
it was my turn to protect him now.

228
00:16:17,340 --> 00:16:19,880
But it turned out
that it was none of my concern.

229
00:16:22,032 --> 00:16:23,822
Did Flying Squirrel tell you that?

230
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:28,203
"Your life is your business.

231
00:16:28,838 --> 00:16:30,838
And my life is mine.

232
00:16:31,669 --> 00:16:33,879
We are walking on separate paths.

233
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:35,740
Leave it that way."

234
00:16:37,477 --> 00:16:39,237
So... speaking of...

235
00:16:39,802 --> 00:16:41,132
How is he doing now?

236
00:16:54,507 --> 00:16:56,887
I'm the one who bothered her.

237
00:16:57,661 --> 00:16:58,541
So why?

238
00:16:59,421 --> 00:17:02,051
She feels that she has said too much.

239
00:17:02,901 --> 00:17:04,821
So she wants to apologize to you.

240
00:17:08,831 --> 00:17:09,791
Good evening.

241
00:17:10,356 --> 00:17:11,316
Welcome.

242
00:17:22,545 --> 00:17:23,375
Well...

243
00:17:23,896 --> 00:17:26,406
I was ignorant and insensitive.

244
00:17:26,669 --> 00:17:28,669
I am really sorry. I shouldn't have...

245
00:17:33,041 --> 00:17:34,671
"We got your back.

246
00:17:35,428 --> 00:17:36,268
So...

247
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:38,185
don't run. Just fight."

248
00:17:41,986 --> 00:17:42,826
Harumi,

249
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:46,633
I will tell him everything myself.
You got that?

250
00:17:47,409 --> 00:17:50,369
Whatever you want.
I'm leaving after my meal.

251
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:52,147
You are so unsociable.

252
00:17:52,296 --> 00:17:54,046
I stopped meddling in others' affairs.

253
00:17:56,957 --> 00:17:58,417
Don't you recognize me?

254
00:18:07,014 --> 00:18:08,394
Crimson Maple and...

255
00:18:10,935 --> 00:18:12,105
Crimson Maple and...

256
00:18:13,271 --> 00:18:14,101
Flying Squirrel?

257
00:18:15,523 --> 00:18:16,733
You're Flying Squirrel.

258
00:18:18,787 --> 00:18:20,280
Really? Really?

259
00:18:21,239 --> 00:18:22,218
Flying...

260
00:18:22,218 --> 00:18:23,241
Want some water?

261
00:18:32,621 --> 00:18:33,788
Flying Squirrel?

262
00:18:34,914 --> 00:18:36,374
Get ready.

263
00:18:36,588 --> 00:18:38,848
We're live,
so please watch your language.

264
00:18:40,139 --> 00:18:42,509
The commercial break will end soon.

265
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:47,060
Shima, go.

266
00:18:48,039 --> 00:18:50,879
This is "Midnight Shima-chan."

267
00:18:51,582 --> 00:18:54,832
Believe it or not,
I have a special guest tonight.

268
00:18:55,269 --> 00:18:58,116
Honestly, I didn't think
that he would come.

269
00:18:58,116 --> 00:18:59,760
Long time no see.

270
00:19:00,568 --> 00:19:03,578
I'm Black Flying Squirrel
from Super Ninja Squadron Koga.

271
00:19:03,779 --> 00:19:07,329
I'm so happy to hear
that everyone remembers me.

272
00:19:14,681 --> 00:19:17,101
I'm the only one here today,

273
00:19:17,101 --> 00:19:18,905
but get ready for our usual callout.

274
00:19:18,905 --> 00:19:21,163
"When the five super ninjas unite,

275
00:19:21,163 --> 00:19:23,664
they kill evildoers, leaving no trace!

276
00:19:23,991 --> 00:19:26,289
When five bells ring,

277
00:19:26,289 --> 00:19:28,405
time's up for the evildoers.

278
00:19:28,405 --> 00:19:30,733
Koga will go anywhere

279
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:34,217
beyond good and evil!"

280
00:19:40,286 --> 00:19:42,786
Can you believe
today's show is almost over?

281
00:19:43,496 --> 00:19:48,086
Flying Squirrel wants to send a message
to his dear friend.

282
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:57,795
I will send out a personal message
through the radio.

283
00:19:59,259 --> 00:20:03,849
I love who I am, as well as who I was.

284
00:20:07,402 --> 00:20:11,032
No matter what others say about me,
I don't care. This is who I am.

285
00:20:12,239 --> 00:20:15,869
I may have a thicker skin now
than I had then...

286
00:20:19,352 --> 00:20:20,312
That said...

287
00:20:22,561 --> 00:20:24,021
I appreciate the fact...

288
00:20:25,646 --> 00:20:27,026
that you care about me.

289
00:20:29,806 --> 00:20:32,806
I want to thank you sincerely.

290
00:20:39,362 --> 00:20:41,532
Please come again, Flying Squirrel.

291
00:20:42,490 --> 00:20:43,780
Until next week.

292
00:20:44,398 --> 00:20:45,608
Good night, everyone.

293
00:20:59,762 --> 00:21:01,342
I'm sorry. I didn't see you.

294
00:21:02,202 --> 00:21:03,752
Where are you going?

295
00:21:35,381 --> 00:21:36,631
Here you go.

296
00:21:39,714 --> 00:21:42,754
I'm the sixth Super Ninja,
White Shima-chan.

297
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:45,926
My favorite item is "with noodles"
after all.

298
00:21:46,471 --> 00:21:48,181
Hey rookie, no whispering.

299
00:21:48,577 --> 00:21:49,407
Yes, ma'am.

300
00:21:50,871 --> 00:21:52,331
Attention please, everyone.

301
00:21:53,033 --> 00:21:54,573
Good night.

302
00:23:40,921 --> 00:23:45,890
THIS STORY IS FICTION

